The paper deals with the construction and routing of geometric graphs in the plane, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of angle-monotone paths is also related to data structures (cs.DS) and network algorithms (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the spanning properties of angle-monotone graphs, which is a topic in structural informatics (cs.SI) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM).
